Mesosoma (
Fig. 10
): mesoscutum 1.2–1.3 times as long as wide, with or without median weakly raised line; scutellum 1.4–1.6 times as long as distance between lateral carinae at its base, lateral carina fading out beyond middle of scutellum; propodeum trans-striate on median portion, with sublateral crest present.

Metasoma with 1 st tergum 2.3–2.8 times as long as apical width and 1.3–1.5 times as long as 2 nd; male subgenital plate (
Fig. 16
) short with apical margin moderately convex; paramere (
Fig. 17
) subelliptic, with apical portions of dorsal and ventral margins slightly emarginate; hairs on lamina volsellaris weak and sparse; apex of digitus truncate with coners rounded, without teeth; median portion of membrane of median surface with weakly papillate area, area not sclerotized; pad semicircular and situated at apical 1 / 6 of paramere in middle; median subapical sclerotized plate transverse, not produced to form an overhang; penis valve (
Fig. 18
) broad, somewhat broadened toward apex, with subapical portion strongly curved ventrally; basal apodeme of aedeagus strongly curved dorsally.
